senses.sense_definition: A thin strip of food, usually fish or chicken, that is typically coated in breadcrumbs and deep-fried.

examples.text: I ordered a basket of chicken <w>goujons</w> and chips for lunch.
The restaurant serves crispy sole <w>goujons</w> with a side of tartare sauce.

senses.sense_definition: A small freshwater fish, commonly known as a gudgeon.

examples.text: The angler sat by the stream hoping to catch a few small <w>goujons</w>.
In some regions, fried <w>goujons</w> are considered a traditional river delicacy.
